ieved a fiscal balance if the deficit is between -1.5 per cent and 1.5 per cent, prior to the crisis, nine of these twelve countries had achieved either fiscal balances or surpluses (Table II-2). But the crisis soon took its toll and by 2008 only six were still in balance. The rest were running moderate to high deficits and for five of these \u2013 India, Kazakhstan, Mongolia, Papua New Guinea, and Samoa \u2013 the deficit increased by more than 1.5 percentage points. Mongolia was hit particularly hard, switching from a 5 per cent surplus to a 2 per cent deficit. All of them expect a higher deficit (or lower surplus) in 2009 compared with 2008, and seven expect to run a budget deficit in excess of 3.5 per cent of GDP, the level beyond which sustainability is likely to be undermined.", "start_char_idx": null, "end_char_idx": null, "text_template": "{metadata_str}\n\n{content}", "metadata_template": "{key}: {value}", "metadata_seperator": "\n"}, "__type__": "1"}, "fa171351-7cbf-4a9c-9cce-08b406672f80": {"__data__": {"id_": "fa171351-7cbf-4a9c-9cce-08b406672f80", "embedding": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-mdg-report-2009/2010", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "excluded_embed_metadata_keys": [], "excluded_llm_metadata_keys": [], "relationships": {"1": {"node_id": "Asia-Pacific MDG Report 2009/2010", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-mdg-report-2009/2010", "Author": "United Nations Development Programme", "Publisher": "United Nations Development Programme", "Type": "Report"}, "hash": "029311512afb2b64ded02816a7059e70f01226e6c106487a3cf433cca440ed16"}, "2": {"node_id": "84f5bacf-6918-47b4-8c58-5a548b4f714f", "node_type": null, "metadata": {"Title_URL": "https://www.undp.org/asia-pacific/publications/asia-pacific-mdg-report-2009/2010", "Author": "Unite